How to Use for New Region:

  Step 1: Upload script to EC2
  scp -i your-key.pem scripts/wg-setup.sh ubuntu@<EC2-IP>:~/

  Step 2: Run with custom BASE_IP
  ssh -i your-key.pem ubuntu@<EC2-IP>

  chmod +x wg-setup.sh

  # For Canada region (use 10.40.0)
  sudo ./wg-setup.sh 10.40.0

  # For Tokyo region (use 10.30.0)
  sudo ./wg-setup.sh 10.30.0

  # For any other region (use 10.50.0, 10.60.0, etc.)
  sudo ./wg-setup.sh 10.50.0

  Step 3: Copy output to .env

  The script will output something like:
  ================================================
  ğŸ“‹ COPY THESE VALUES TO YOUR .env FILE:
  ================================================
  REGION_XX_ID=<your-region-id>
  REGION_XX_NAME=<Your Region Name>
  REGION_XX_HOST=13.229.xxx.xxx
  REGION_XX_ENDPOINT=13.229.xxx.xxx:51820
  REGION_XX_SERVER_PUBLIC_KEY=AbCdEfGhIjKlMnOpQrStUvWxYz1234567890ABCDEF=
  REGION_XX_BASE_IP=10.40.0
  ================================================

  Just replace XX with your region prefix (CA, SG, US, etc.)!

